race.comment: MR FERRARI (9) doesn't win out of turn but is edging closer and looks destined to break through soon. Draws to get every favour and should be in this for a very long way. Holds his form and he's right in the finish. SCANDALIST (10) hasn't threatened yet this prep but has been building steadily. Finds a far more suitable assignment here and draws well for Crowther. A bold showing is very much on the cards. REVOLUTION BELLE (7) couldn't match a sharp winner at Oakbank last start but stuck on honestly for a midfield finish. On the quick back-up and capable of improving. ZOULAR (4) fought on gamely at Nhill to finish within a length in a tight finish. This is a touch tougher, but he gets weight relief and remains in the mix.
